Load required libraries

library(maptools)
library(rgeos)
library(RColorBrewer)
library(ggplot2)
library(plyr)
library(rgdal)
library(ggmap)
library(mapview)

Load shapefile

shape <- readShapeSpatial(
  "//ad.monash.edu/home/User085/acharett/Desktop/ubuntu_shared/map/district.shp")

Arrange data

shape1 <- fortify(shape)
shape$id <- row.names(shape)
shape2 = merge(x = shape1, y = shape@data, by = "id", all.x = TRUE)

Make map

map = ggplot(shape2, aes(x = long, y = lat, group=group, fill = average_ho)) + 
  geom_polygon(color='black',size=0.05)+
  coord_fixed()+
  theme_bw()+
  labs(x='',y='', fill="Average number\n of households")
map+scale_fill_gradient(low = "white", high = "blue")

Make map with Color Brewer

new_fill<- function(pal, lowerlim, upperlim){
  scale_fill_gradientn(colours= pal, limits=c(lowerlim, upperlim))
}
map+new_fill(brewer.pal(7, "Blues"), 2.25, 3.5)

Overlay map on ggogle map basemap

map <- readOGR("//ad.monash.edu/home/User085/acharett/Desktop/ubuntu_shared/map", "district", verbose =FALSE)
map_wgs84 <- spTransform(map, CRS("+proj=longlat +datum=WGS84"))
shape1 <- fortify(map_wgs84)
map_wgs84$id <- row.names(map_wgs84)
shape2 = merge(x = shape1, y = shape@data, by = "id", all.x = TRUE)
map2 <- qmap("Syndal, Glen Waverley", zoom = 14,source = "google", maptype = "hybrid")
map2 <- map2 +
  geom_polygon(data= shape2, aes(x = long, y = lat, group=group,fill = average_ho),
               color='black',size=0.05, alpha =0.5)+
  labs(x='',y='', fill="Average number\n of households\n")+
  theme(legend.title = element_text(size=12, face="bold"))
map2 + new_fill(brewer.pal(7, "Blues"), 2.25, 3.5)

Create online interactive map

mapviewOptions(vector.palette = colorRampPalette(brewer.pal(9, "YlGnBu")))
names(map_wgs84@data)[2]<-"Average households"
mapview(map_wgs84, zcol = c("Average households"), alpha= (0.9), legend = TRUE)
